### Observed behavior
Our app is located behind a security gateway and is using a service worker. The service worker was integrated following [this guide](https://angular.io/guide/service-worker-getting-started). Because of the fact that *any* request is passed through the security gateway we had to provide additional options to the construction of any `Request` object, namely `credentials` and `mode`, when a service worker is requesting its manifest from the server. Otherwise manifest fetch fails with CORS error:

> No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is present on the requested resource.

